summary:
• FY2025 results announcement date: 21 August 2025
  • FY2025 annual report publication date: 30 September 2025
  • Annual Meeting date: 13 November 2025 (virtual/in-person, Ashburton, NZ)
  • Closing date for director nominations: 15 September 2025 (5:00pm NZST)

No material financial or operational information disclosed.

Key Material Information:

  • FY25 Hydro Generation: 3,410 GWh (17% lower than PCP), 4th lowest since 1980 due to 12th percentile Waikato inflows and low Lake Taupō levels.
  • FY26+ Mean Hydro Uplift: Increased to 4,140 GWh/year (+62 GWh) from Digital River (AI optimization) and Karāpiro Rehabilitation Project.
  • Karāpiro Hydro Upgrade: Third unit completion Sep-25, adding 16.5MW capacity (+32 GWh/year at average inflows).
  • FY25 Total Generation: 7,906 GWh (11% ↓ PCP), with wind (6% ↓) and geothermal (2% ↓) also lower.
  • Market Prices: Spot avg. $216/MWh (Auckland); FY26-27 forwards at $179/MWh (as of 30 Jun-25).

Omitted: Market share stats, operational minutiae.

Index Change Announcement:
- Infratil Limited (IFT) to be added to the S&P/ASX 200 Index, effective 23 July 2025 (pre-market open).
- Spartan Resources Limited (SPR) to be removed (due to acquisition by Ramelius Resources).

No other material information identified.

Here is the concise extraction of material information from Meridian Energy's June 2025 operating report:

Key Operational Highlights:
- Hydro Storage: National hydro storage increased from 94% to 104% of historical average (June–14 July 2025). South Island storage at 95%, North Island at 150% of average.
- Generation Metrics:
- June 2025 generation +6.1% YoY (hydro + wind). FY25 generation -6.0% YoY.
- Average generation price in June: -54.2% YoY ($121.0/MWh). FY25 average price +7.3% YoY.
- Retail Sales: June volumes +7.9% YoY; residential (+12.7%), large business (+15.2%). FY25 volumes -0.9% YoY.
- NZ Aluminium Smelter (NZAS): Agreement to end 50MW demand response by 11 August 2025. June load: 530MW (vs. 394MW in June 2024).
- Costs: FY25 operating costs -0.2% YoY; capex -16.5% YoY.

Market Data:
- Electricity futures prices declined in Q4 2025, with winter quarters falling.
- National demand: June +1.4% YoY, Q4 -2.6% YoY.

Valuation Impact:
1. Price Pressure: Lower generation prices (-18.6% YoY in Q4) and declining futures suggest earnings headwinds.
2. Customer Growth: Retail connections +9.6% YoY, supporting revenue resilience despite volume declines.

No capital raising, dividends, or liquidity events disclosed.
Omitted: Routine weather data, non-material segment details.
